Concerns have been raised for a 12-year-old girl missing from home for nearly 24 hours. Brooklyn Nash was last seen in her hometown of Southport, Merseyside. Her loved ones raised the alarm when she vanished around 4pm on Saturday. Those who saw her yesterday say she was wearing a grey hoodie, black leggings and pink Air Jordan trainers. She has links to the Manchester area and Liverpool City Centre area, including Williamson Square. Anyone who sees Brooklyn is asked to contact Merseyside Police. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.